{"lemma":"ساجُ","slug":"ساجُ","root":"س.#.ج","root_slug":"س-_-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19017","n21142"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%AC%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"teak tree and wood (Tectona gen. et spp.)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Aramaic שָׁאגָא / שָׁגָא / ܫܓܐ (šāgā), Persian ساج (sâj). Ultimately from Sanskrit शाक (śāka, “vegetable; herb; teak-tree”); compare vernacular Hindi सागौन (sāgaun, “teak-tree”) and Bengali সেগুন (śegun, “teak-tree”) for the consonantism."},"ipa":["/saːd͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19017","headword_ar":"سَاجٍ","root":"sjw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Still, silent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quiet:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus applied to the sea [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unruffled"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN saAjiyapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ سَاجِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calm night, in which the wind is still, and such as is not dark:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a night in which the cold has become allayed, and in which the wind and the clouds have become still, and which is not dark."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarofN saAjK","text_ar":"طَرْفٌ سَاجٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A still,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"motionless, eye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EayonN saAjiyapN","text_ar":"عَيْنٌ سَاجِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to IAar, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an eye that has a languid,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"languishing, look;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is an accessory to beauty in women. (TA.) See also the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":["T","TA","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n21142","headword_ar":"سَاجٌ","root":"swj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"teak-tree; tectona grandis;"},{"kind":"text","text":"to which the name of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAj","text_ar":"ساج"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied in Pers.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remarkable for its huge size, and enormous leaves:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Indian,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Oriental, plane-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Indian plantain-tree:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see De Sacy's Chrest. Ar., sec. ed., iii. 473:)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain species of tree,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of great size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"growing to a very great size,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that grows only in India, and is conveyed thence to other countries;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) so they say: (Mgh:) Z says, (Msb,) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a black, heavy, wood, which is brought from India,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in pieces made of an oblong form, and squared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and which the woodfretter can hardly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not at all, wear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waste;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb;) and he says that its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyjaAnN","text_ar":"سِيجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb: [but this is said in the A only to be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAj","text_ar":"ساج"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ a rounded, wide,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasaAn","text_ar":"طَيْلَسَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": ”]) some say that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it resembles ebony, but is less black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) accord to the A, Noah's ark was made of it: but several authors say that it is related in the Book of the Law revealed to Moses that it was made of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sanawobar","text_ar":"صَنَوْبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or pine-tree]; and some say that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Snwbr","text_ar":"صنوبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a species of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAj","text_ar":"ساج"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) AHn describes it, (O, TA,) on the authority of one who had seen it in its places of growth, (O,) as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of tree that grows to a great size, tall and wide, having leaves like the shields of the Deylem"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ayolam","text_ar":"الدَّيْلَم"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with one of which leaves a man may cover himself, and it will protect him from the rain, and it has a sweet odour, like the odour of the leaves of the walnut, and is fine and soft,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smooth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the elephants"},{"kind":"text","text":"[he says]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are fond of it, and of the leaves of the banana, both of which they eat: it is not of the trees that grow in the land of the Arabs, nor does it grow in any country except those of India and the Zenj; nor does any tree grow so tall, nor any so big:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAjapN","text_ar":"سَاجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.; and its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAjaAtN","text_ar":"سَاجَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of wood of the tree called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAj","text_ar":"ساج"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of an oblong form, and squared, as brought from India;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * Mgh, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is cut and prepared for a foundation and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsi binaAy^ihi saAjapN","text_ar":"اَسَاسِ بِنَايِهِ سَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the foundation of his building is a piece of wood of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAj","text_ar":"ساج"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut in an oblong form, and squared"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAjp","text_ar":"ساجة"},{"kind":"text","text":"from which a door is cloven, or divided off lengthwise, is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliyjapN","text_ar":"سَلِيجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) and the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAjapN","text_ar":"سَاجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"board,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tablet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of wood of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAj","text_ar":"ساج"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which stand"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or rest"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the two scales of the balance when one weighs with it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham. p. 818.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1460},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TayolasaAn","text_ar":"طَيْلَسَان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ashy, dust-colour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, A, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a black"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (IAar, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large, thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of a round form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and wide:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hollowed out in the middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muqaw~arN","text_ar":"مُقَوَّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":");"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so woven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, O, Msb:) this last is said to be meant in a trad. in which it is said that the Prophet used to wear in war such"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalaAnis","text_ar":"قَلَانِس"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalanosuwapN","text_ar":"قَلَنْسُوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,] as were [made] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyjaAn","text_ar":"سِيجَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siyjaAnN","text_ar":"سِيجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl.: (T, S, A, O, Msb:) the dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwayojN","text_ar":"سُوَيْجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) It is tropically applied to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisaA='","text_ar":"كِسَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made of a square form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four-sided;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is described as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHafap","text_ar":"مِلْحَفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"woven."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) As meaning a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TylsAn","text_ar":"طيلسان"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is said by some, that its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L, TA.) ―         -b2-  It is also used, by a poet, in the manner of an epithet, as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of the colour termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuDorap","text_ar":"خُضْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[expl. above]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","IAar","Az","T"]}]}}